{
  "texts": [
    "Some comments are in order.",
    "Firstly, thanks to Proposition 2.9, flatness in (i) yields an isomorphism M ≃ B × ρ N, and by Proposition 2.14 the bundle metric becomes a ρ-equivariant map h: B → Sym 2 + (𝔫 *).",
    "The monodromy assumption has two parts: on one hand, there is no translational part (cf.",
    "On the other hand, the unimodularity restriction on ρ further ensures the existence of a globally-defined, ∇ ad -parallel density |ν ad | on the fibres of adM.Next, when lifted to M ≃ B × N, a metric g satisfying Ansatz 3.1 is of the form g = gB + h, and by (ii), the fibres (N, h b) are all nilsolitons.",
    "The significance of the condition ∇ ad (h -1 Ric h) = 0 is that the Ricci endomorphism of the fibres is independent of the B-coordinate."
